fields.comment: This field will be required for use whenever a Profile is being used.

fields.description: Software Certified Version or Release Number

fields.comment: Unique to each query message instance.

The combination of values for Patientlist.ID, patientlst.identifiercode and Patientlist.AssigningAuthority are intended to allow unique identification of a client, if the data are found in the responding system.
If this field, PID.5, is not valued, then the query will return an error, since this is a required field.
If this field, PID.6, is not valued, Mothers maiden name is not considered when seeking matching clients.
If this field, PID.7, is not valued to an accuracy of at least day, then this field is considered not valued.
If this field, PID.8, is not valued, then all values for this field are considered a match.
If this field, PID.11, is not valued, then address will not be considered when seeking matching clients.
This field will be considered the Home phone. If this field, PID.13, is not valued, then phone number is not considered when seeking matching clients.
If this field, PID.24, is not valued, then Multiple Birth Indicator is not considered when seeking matching clients.
If this field, PID.25, is not valued, then birth order is not considered when seeking matching clients.
If this field, PID.33, is not valued, then client last updated date is not considered when seeking matching clients.
If this field, PID.34, is not valued, then client last updating facility is not considered when seeking matching clients.
This field may contain a maximum number of records that may be returned. The first component contains the count and the second contains "RD" for records.
This field will be required for use whenever a Profile is being used.
